  ('Single-Leg Cone Reach Stick', 'single-leg-cone-reach-stick', 'Single-Leg Cone Reach Stick is a cone-based athletic drill focused on foot tripod, hip control, and single-leg ownership. One athlete stands inside a small triangle of cones and reaches to touch each cone. It belongs in the library because it is easy to set up, easy to coach, and scalable from youth development to advanced field/court athletes.', 'BEGINNER', 6, 2, 3, NULL, 60, 40, 'individual', 'Cone drill for foot tripod, hip control, and single-leg ownership. Best when coached as Resilience with the drill dose matched to the session phase.', 'Primary phase: Resilience. Primary subrole: single_leg_balance_foot_ankle_hip_control. Control, braking, and tissue tolerance; speed is secondary to clean ownership. Progress only when the route, posture, and stop/cut quality are repeatable.', 'Move in under control, stick the stop, and own the position.', 'Single-Leg Cone Control', 'resilience', 'single_leg_balance_foot_ankle_hip_control', 'single_leg_cone_reach', '{"primary_joint_actions":["ankle_stiffness","deceleration_braking","hip_flexion_extension","hip_hinge_absorption","knee_flexion_extension"],"primary_tissues":["calves","quadriceps","hamstrings","glutes","adductors"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["braking_control","single_leg_stability","spatial_orientation","visual_navigation"],"postural_shape":"athletic stance with ribs stacked over pelvis during cuts and stops","breathing_demand":"rhythmic; no breath holding during approach, cut, or stop","balance_demand":"dynamic","coordination_demand":"multi-step cone navigation with clean arm-leg timing","impact_level":1}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Single-Leg Cone Reach Stick uses cones to create a clear movement problem: foot tripod, hip control, and single-leg ownership. One athlete stands inside a small triangle of cones and reaches to touch each cone. The coach selects speed, spacing, and rest so the drill trains resilience rather than junk fatig